subnotes/erinyes-or-furies-复仇女神.html.description:
three goddesses who punished&nbsp;the crimes of those who escaped or defied(藐视) public justice by their secret stings The heads of the Furies were wreathed(缠绕) with serpents and their appearance was terrific and appalling
they are Alecto,&nbsp;Tisiphone and Megæra．
They were&nbsp;also called Eumenides&nbsp;
